# Git Commands Used in the Assignment

## 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<username>/MLOPS-assignment-1.git
cd MLOPS-assignment-1
```

## 2. Create Decision Tree Branch

```bash
git checkout -b dtree
```

## 3. Add Project Files

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push -u origin dtree
```

## 4. Create Kernel Ridge Branch

```bash
git checkout main
git checkout -b kernelridge
```

## 5. Add Kernel Ridge Model

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Add Kernel Ridge Model"
git push -u origin kernelridge
```

## 6. Resolve README Merge Conflict

```bash
git add README.md
git commit -m "Resolve README conflict"
git push -u origin main
```

## 7. Create GitHub Actions CI Pipeline

```bash
git add .github/workflows/ci.yml
git commit -m "Add GitHub Actions CI pipeline"
git push origin kernelridge
```

## 8. Create Pull Request and Merge

Kernel Ridge Branch → Main Branch

Pull Request Title:

Add Kernel Ridge Model

After successful CI execution, the pull request was merged into the main branch.

## 9. Verify Branches

```bash
git branch
```

Output:

```bash
dtree
kernelridge
main
```

## 10. Check Repository Status

```bash
git status
```

## 11. Pull Latest Changes

```bash
git pull origin main
```

## 12. Push Changes

```bash
git push origin main
git push origin dtree
git push origin kernelridge
```
